# Vercel deploy readiness (required)

All changes must preserve the ability to deploy this project on **Vercel** without issues.

## Required behavior

- Ensure the project **builds successfully** in a clean environment (no reliance on untracked local files or globally installed tools).
- Prefer **Vercel-compatible** runtime patterns (serverless/edge constraints, stateless execution).
- Treat environment configuration as deploy-time concerns:
  - document required env vars
  - avoid hardcoding secrets/URLs
  - provide safe defaults where appropriate
- Keep platform-specific assumptions out of core logic (filesystem, long-lived background processes, local-only paths).

## Avoid

- Writing to the repo filesystem at runtime as a persistence mechanism.
- Assuming long-running stateful processes, local daemons, or OS-specific tooling will exist in production.
- Changes that require manual post-deploy steps to function.

